OpenKeychain打开钥匙串

OpenKeychain helps you communicate more privately and securely. It uses encryption to ensure that your messages can be read only by the people you send them to, others can send you messages that only you can read, and these messages can be digitally signed so the people getting them are sure who sent them. OpenKeychain is based on the well established OpenPGP standard making encryption compatible across your devices and systems. For a list of compatible software for Windows, Mac OS, and other operating systems consult openpgp.org/software/.OpenKeychain 可帮助您更私密、更安全地进行交流。它使用加密来确保您的消息只能由您发送给他们的人阅读，其他人可以向您发送只有您可以阅读的消息，并且这些消息可以进行数字签名，以便接收它们的人确定是谁发送的。 OpenKeychain 基于完善的 OpenPGP 标准，使加密在您的设备和系统之间兼容。有关适用于 Windows、Mac OS 和其他操作系统的兼容软件列表，请访问 openpgp.org/software/。

Modern encryption is based on digital “keys”. OpenKeychain stores and manages your keys, and those of the people you communicate with, on your Android smartphone. It also helps you find others’ keys online, and exchange keys. But its most frequent use is in using those keys to encrypt and decrypt messages.现代加密基于数字“密钥”。 OpenKeychain 在您的 Android 智能手机上存储和管理您的密钥以及与您通信的人的密钥。它还可以帮助您在线查找其他人的密钥，并交换密钥。但它最常见的用途是使用这些密钥来加密和解密消息。

Open Source开源

Open Source: OpenKeychain is designed to be trustworthy. It’s Free Software with no secrets; anyone can examine and validate every bit of it (Source code available at GitHub)开源：OpenKeychain 旨在值得信赖。它是没有秘密的免费软件；任何人都可以检查和验证它​​的每一点（GitHub 上提供源代码）

Independent Security Audit独立安全审计

The auditing company Cure53 performed an intensive security audit of OpenKeychain. The security experts summarize their final result with “[…] none of the spotted issues were considered to be of a critical severity in terms of security implications. The latter is a significant and impressive result for an app of this complexity and relevance.”审计公司 Cure53 对 OpenKeychain 进行了深入的安全审计。安全专家将他们的最终结果总结为“[...] 就安全影响而言，没有一个发现的问题被认为具有严重的严重性。对于具有这种复杂性和相关性的应用程序来说，后者是一个重要而令人印象深刻的结果。”

Permissions权限

Because OpenKeychain is Free Software, anyone can validate that the permissions are indeed only required for the listed features.因为 OpenKeychain 是免费软件，所以任何人都可以验证确实只有列出的功能需要权限。

  • In-app purchases: Donate to the developers应用内购买：捐赠给开发者
  • Identity: Pre-fill name and email addresses身份：预填姓名和电子邮件地址
  • Contacts: Connect keys to your contacts (only offline)联系人：将密钥连接到您的联系人（仅限离线）
  • Photos/Media/Files: Import/export keys from SD card照片/媒体/文件：从 SD 卡导入/导出密钥
  • Camera: Scan QR Codes to add other people’s keys相机：扫描二维码添加其他人的钥匙
  • Others: Internet permission to retrieve keys, NFC permission to use YubiKeys其他：检索密钥的互联网权限，使用 YubiKeys 的 NFC 权限

Starting with Android 6, permissions are requested when required in-app!从 Android 6 开始，在应用内需要时请求权限！

Frequently Asked Questions经常问的问题

Are my secret keys safe on my mobile device?我的密钥在我的移动设备上安全吗？

This is a very common question, and it’s not an easy one. In the end it comes down to how much you trust your mobile device. The real question usually isn’t, “how safe are they”, but rather “are they less safe than on my laptop”? The answer depends on three factors:这是一个很常见的问题，也不是一个简单的问题。最后，这取决于您对移动设备的信任程度。真正的问题通常不是“它们有多安全”，而是“它们是否不如我的笔记本电脑安全”？答案取决于三个因素：

  1. Do you trust the hardware? Obviously, there are no guarantees that the vendor of your phone hardware didn’t add some kind of backdoor. Then again, the same applies to your laptop’s hardware, so it’s about even.你相信硬件吗？显然，无法保证您的手机硬件供应商没有添加某种后门。再一次，这同样适用于你的笔记本电脑的硬件，所以它是均匀的。
  2. How easily can the device be stolen? This depends a lot on how careful you are, but this too is probably about even with your laptop.设备被盗有多容易？这在很大程度上取决于您的谨慎程度，但这也可能与您的笔记本电脑有关。
  3. Do you trust the software? The Android operating system actually offers a lot more in the way of security between applications than desktop operating systems. No app without root privileges besides OpenKeychain can ever access the keys stored in OpenKeychain’s database. By comparison, any program you run on your computer can just upload your gnupg keyring, if those files belong to the same user. As long as Android as a platform is trustworthy, your keys are safe from malware apps.你相信这个软件吗？与桌面操作系统相比，Android 操作系统实际上在应用程序之间提供了更多的安全方式。除了 OpenKeychain 之外，没有 root 权限的任何应用程序都无法访问存储在 OpenKeychain 数据库中的密钥。相比之下，如果这些文件属于同一用户，您在计算机上运行的任何程序都可以上传您的 gnupg 密钥环。只要 Android 作为平台值得信赖，您的密钥就不会受到恶意软件应用程序的侵害。

In conclusion, we believe that secret keys are not notably less safe on your mobile than they would be on your laptop. If your security requirements are high enough that you don’t keep your keys on your laptop, you probably shouldn’t put them on your mobile either. Otherwise, they should be fine.总之，我们认为密钥在您的手机上并不比在笔记本电脑上安全得多。如果您的安全要求足够高以至于您不会将密钥放在笔记本电脑上，那么您可能也不应该将它们放在手机上。否则，他们应该没问题。

How to import an OpenKeychain backup with gpg?如何使用 gpg 导入 OpenKeychain 备份？

  1. Make a backup from OpenKeychain and transfer it to your computer via email or a cloud provider, like Dropbox. This is safe because OpenKeychain backups are encrypted with Advanced Encryption Standard (AES) using securely generated Backup Codes.从 OpenKeychain 备份并通过电子邮件或云提供商（如 Dropbox）将其传输到您的计算机。这是安全的，因为 OpenKeychain 备份是使用安全生成的备份代码使用高级加密标准 (AES) 加密的。

  2. On your PC, execute the following line:在您的 PC 上，执行以下行：

    # replace 'backup_YYYY-MM-DD.pgp' with the name of your backup file
gpg --decrypt backup_YYYY-MM-DD.pgp | gpg --import
  3. Enter the full Backup Code including the dashes, e.g., “1234-5678-9012-3456-7890-1234-5678-9012-3456”输入完整的备份代码，包括破折号，例如“1234-5678-9012-3456-7890-1234-5678-9012-3456”

What is the best way to transfer my own key to OpenKeychain?将我自己的密钥传输到 OpenKeychain 的最佳方式是什么？

Short answer:简短回答：

# generate a strong random password
gpg --armor --gen-random 1 20

# encrypt key, use password above when asked
gpg --armor --export-secret-keys YOUREMAILADDRESS | gpg --armor --symmetric --output mykey.sec.asc

Longer answer:更长的答案：

You should make sure that your key can’t be intercepted during transfer. If you have an SD-Card reader in your phone, you can use this to easily transfer your key. If you don’t, you can transfer your key through an online service (such as E-Mail, Dropbox, …), but make sure to encrypt it during transfer!您应该确保您的密钥在传输过程中不会被拦截。如果您的手机中有 SD 卡读卡器，您可以使用它轻松传输您的密钥。如果不这样做，您可以通过在线服务（例如电子邮件、Dropbox 等）传输您的密钥，但请确保在传输过程中对其进行加密！

To transfer your key to OpenKeychain from gpg, the best way to do so is to encrypt it with a single-use password, which you never use anywhere else and never send online. Use gpg as shown above to generate a random password, then export and encrypt your key with it.要将您的密钥从 gpg 传输到 OpenKeychain，最好的方法是使用一次性密码对其进行加密，您永远不会在其他任何地方使用该密码，也永远不会在线发送。如上所示使用 gpg 生成随机密码，然后导出并使用它加密您的密钥。

Once the key is encrypted, transfer the file to your mobile using any method, decrypt the file with OpenKeychain. When asked, manually (!) input the password.密钥加密后，使用任何方法将文件传输到您的手机，使用 OpenKeychain 解密文件。当询问时，手动（！）输入密码。

Do not use a weak password! This method is only safe if the password you use is very strong (like 20 random, alphanumeric characters), and humans are really bad at generating random strings. Use gpg as shown above, or another random password generator of your choice.不要使用弱密码！仅当您使用的密码非常强（如 20 个随机的字母数字字符）时，此方法才是安全的，并且人类真的不擅长生成随机字符串。如上所示使用 gpg，或您选择的其他随机密码生成器。

Do not use an online password generator! This beats the purpose of using a generated password in the first place! An attacker who can get the file from your Dropbox account, can likely also see the Website you got the password from!不要使用在线密码生成器！这首先超出了使用生成密码的目的！可以从您的 Dropbox 帐户获取文件的攻击者也可能会看到您从中获取密码的网站！

Should I confirm a key without manually comparing fingerprints?我是否应该在不手动比较指纹的情况下确认密钥？

To confirm someone’s key, you should make sure that it’s really that same key the other person wants you to confirm with their name on it.要确认某人的密钥，您应该确保它确实是对方希望您用他们的名字确认的那把密钥。

Since keys are usually obtained from a keyserver, it is necessary to double-check that the keyserver gave you the correct key. This is traditionally done by manually comparing the key’s entire fingerprint, character by character.由于密钥通常是从密钥服务器获得的，因此有必要仔细检查密钥服务器是否为您提供了正确的密钥。传统上，这是通过逐个字符地手动比较密钥的整个指纹来完成的。

However, scanning a QR code, receiving a key via NFC, or exchanging keys via SafeSlinger all have that same check already built-in, so as long as you trust the method used for key exchange, there is no reason to check the fingerprint again manually.然而，扫描二维码、通过 NFC 接收密钥或通过 SafeSlinger 交换密钥都已经内置了相同的检查，因此只要您信任用于密钥交换的方法，就没有理由再次检查指纹手动。

Can I mark other keys as trusted, without confirming them with my own key?我可以将其他密钥标记为受信任的，而不用我自己的密钥确认它们吗？

This is not a supported use case. You can, however, simply create a new key which you use for this purpose only, which will essentially be the same thing.这不是受支持的用例。但是，您可以简单地创建一个仅用于此目的的新密钥，这在本质上是相同的。

I see no suitable option in the app selection menu when trying to open a local file, what’s wrong?尝试打开本地文件时，我在应用程序选择菜单中看不到合适的选项，这是怎么回事？

You probably don’t have any stand-alone file managers installed, like OI File Manager or Amaze. OpenKeychain needs one in order to select files from local storage or SD card, such as for importing keys or encrypting/decrypting files.您可能没有安装任何独立的文件管理器，例如 OI 文件管理器或 Amaze。 OpenKeychain 需要一个以便从本地存储或 SD 卡中选择文件，例如导入密钥或加密/解密文件。

NFC Security TokensNFC 安全令牌

What security tokens are recommended for OpenKeychain?OpenKeychain 推荐使用哪些安全令牌？

We currently recommend the YubiKey NEO (50 EUR). It supports USB and NFC.我们目前推荐 YubiKey NEO（50 欧元）。它支持 USB 和 NFC。

Are there other compatible tokens and more information?是否有其他兼容的令牌和更多信息？

We provide a table of currently supported hardware and advanced information on our wiki page.我们在我们的 wiki 页面上提供了当前支持的硬件和高级信息的表格。

Advanced Questions高级问题

Why is OpenKeychain’s database not password protected?为什么 OpenKeychain 的数据库没有密码保护？

Your keys are already encrypted with their password - that’s the reason you have to input it for every crypto operation. There is no point in encrypting those keys again with another password, so password protecting the entire database would only protect the list of keys which are not yours. If this is important to you, consider using full disk encryption.您的密钥已经使用密码加密 - 这就是您必须为每个加密操作输入密码的原因。用另一个密码再次加密这些密钥是没有意义的，因此保护整个数据库的密码只会保护不属于您的密钥列表。如果这对您很重要，请考虑使用全盘加密。

Why is my password requested when I backup my keys?为什么在备份密钥时需要我的密码？

It is not required cryptographically, but prevents simple stealing of your keys.它不需要加密，但可以防止简单地窃取您的密钥。

Everyone can delete my keys. Why is there no password request before?每个人都可以删除我的密钥。为什么之前没有密码请求？

Anyone who can physically access your device can simply delete the app data from Android OS. Also, asking for a password before delete would prevent you from deleting keys where you forgot your password任何可以物理访问您设备的人都可以简单地从 Android 操作系统中删除应用程序数据。此外，在删除前询问密码会阻止您删除忘记密码的密钥

I have more than one subkey capable of signing. Which one is selected when signing with this OpenPGP key?我有不止一个能够签名的子项。使用此 OpenPGP 密钥签名时选择了哪一个？

OpenKeychain assumes that OpenPGP keys hold one usable signing subkey only and selects the first non-revoked non-expired non-stripped one it finds in the unordered list of subkeys. We consider having more than one valid signing subkey an advanced usecase. You can either strip subkeys that should not be used using OpenKeychain’s edit key screen or explicitly select the right subkeys when exporting from gpg with gpg --export-secret-subkeys.OpenKeychain 假定 OpenPGP 密钥仅包含一个可用的签名子密钥，并选择它在无序列表中找到的第一个未撤销的未过期的未剥离的子密钥。我们认为拥有多个有效签名子密钥是一种高级用例。您可以使用 OpenKeychain 的编辑密钥屏幕去除不应使用的子密钥，或者在使用 gpg --export-secret-subkeys 从 gpg 导出时明确选择正确的子密钥。

Where can I find more information about OpenKeychain’s security model and design decisions?我在哪里可以找到有关 OpenKeychain 的安全模型和设计决策的更多信息？

Head over to our Wiki.前往我们的 Wiki。

Known Issues已知的问题

A wrong primary user id is shown when searching on a Keyserver在密钥服务器上搜索时显示错误的主用户 ID

Unfortunately, this is a bug in the SKS Keyserver software. Its machine-readable output returns the user ids in an arbitrary order. Read the related bug report for more information.不幸的是，这是 SKS Keyserver 软件中的一个错误。它的机器可读输出以任意顺序返回用户 ID。阅读相关的错误报告以获取更多信息。

Not working with AOSP Mail不适用于 AOSP 邮件

For now, OpenKeychain will not support AOSP Mail due to bugs in AOSP which we cannot work around (#290).目前，OpenKeychain 将不支持 AOSP 邮件，因为 AOSP 中存在我们无法解决的错误 (#290)。

API应用程序接口

OpenKeychain provides two APIs, namely the OpenKeychain Intents and the OpenPGP API. The Intents can be used without permissions to start OpenKeychain’s activities for cryptographic operations, import of keys, etc. However, it always requires user input, so that no malicious application can use this API without user intervention. The OpenPGP API is more sophisticated and allows to to operations without user interaction in the background. When utilizing this API, OpenKeychain asks the user on first use to grant access for the calling client application.OpenKeychain 提供了两个 API，即 OpenKeychain Intents 和 OpenPGP API。可以在没有权限的情况下使用 Intent 来启动 OpenKeychain 的加密操作、密钥导入等活动。但是，它始终需要用户输入，因此没有用户干预，任何恶意应用程序都无法使用此 API。 OpenPGP API 更复杂，允许在后台无需用户交互的情况下进行操作。使用此 API 时，OpenKeychain 会在首次使用时要求用户授予调用客户端应用程序的访问权限。

More technical information and examples for these APIs can be found here:有关这些 API 的更多技术信息和示例，请参见此处：

  • OpenKeychain IntentsOpenKeychain 意图
  • OpenPGP APIOpenPGP API
